shows  "ceiling (x powr 2) - (ceiling x) powr 2 = -3"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Evaluate $\lceil (3.6)^2 \rceil - ( \lceil 3.6 \rceil ) ^2$. The final Answer is -3
 ### Proof
 $\lceil (3.6)^2 \rceil = \lceil 12.96 \rceil = 13$ because the least integer greater than $12.96$ is $13$. $( \lceil 3.6 \rceil ) ^2 = 4^2 = 16$ because the least integer greater than $3.6$ is $4$.
 Therefore, the answer is $13-16=\boxed{-3}$.
 *)

fixes x :: real
assumes h0 : "x = 3.6"
shows  "ceiling (x powr 2) - (ceiling x) powr 2 = -3"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
